  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To assess the effect on geriatric patients of follow-up home visit including nutrition.

      The hypothesis is that this can prevent hospital readmissions, and has a positive impact on
      functional abilities and quality of life
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Before and after the intervention the participants nutritional status, hand grip strength,
      functional abilities, well-being, dietary intake, level of tiredness,and activities of daily
      living will be assessed
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
